    → No new visual token choices needed in VacuumPredictionWidget itself
  
  F-P3 (RThermalLiveWidget asymptote line):
    → Prediction line: theme.STATUS_INFO, theme.PLOT_LINE_WIDTH, Qt.DashLine
      (Step 1: matches PredictionWidget canonical convention)
    → CI band: STATUS_INFO at alpha=64 via FillBetweenItem
      (Step 1: matches PredictionWidget canonical convention)
    → No new hex codes. No invented tokens. No design-system modifications.

Source: Step 1 (existing prediction overlay in PredictionWidget) was sufficient.
Steps 2/3/4 not needed — canonical precedent unambiguous.


## Phase 2B/C/D — Implementation complete

F-P1: Pre-existing (no new code). CooldownPredictionWidget + PredictionWidget
  already renders trajectory overlay. Confirmed in recon.

F-P2 implemented: VacuumPredictionWidget (analytics_widgets.py)
  - set_pressure_reading(): accumulates raw pressure buffer (max 5000 pts)
  - _poll_trend(): 10s timer → get_vacuum_trend ZMQ
  - _on_trend_result(): converts relative extrap_t → absolute unix timestamps,
    computes 10^logP mbar values, ±1σ CI band from residual_std
  - Legacy set_vacuum_prediction() path preserved
  - Design tokens: STATUS_INFO, PLOT_LINE_WIDTH, DashLine (via PredictionWidget)

F-P3 implemented: RThermalLiveWidget (analytics_widgets.py)
  - SteadyStatePredictor(window_s=600s, update_interval_s=30s) on R_thermal history
  - pg.LinearRegionItem (horizontal CI band): STATUS_INFO at alpha=64
    [alpha=64 note: no theme.py token for prediction band opacity;
     follows PredictionWidget._CI_BAND_ALPHA=64 convention — Step 1 precedent.
     Missing token logged for architect to add if desired.]
  - pg.InfiniteLine (asymptote line): STATUS_INFO, PLOT_LINE_WIDTH, Qt.DashLine
  - Show when percent_settled >= 30% and valid=True
  - Band width: |amplitude| * (1 - confidence)
  - Only new history timestamps fed to predictor (no duplicates)

Visual audit: no hardcoded hex codes. Only alpha=64 (documented above).

